Package: flaiR
Title: An R Wrapper for Accessing Flair NLP
Version: 0.1.8
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yen-Chieh", "Liao", email = "davidycliao@gmail.com", role = c("cre","aut", "ctb")),
    person("Akbik", "Alan", email = "alan.akbik@zalando.de", role = c("aut", "ctb")),
    person("Blythe", "Duncan", email = "blythe.duncan@zalando.de", role = c("aut", "ctb")),
    person("Vollgraf", "Roland", email = "vollgraf.roland@zalando.de", role = c("aut", "ctb"))
    )
Description: Provides an R interface to the Flair Natural Language Processing  
    library in Python. This package allows R users to access Flair's NLP important features 
    including named entity recognition, part-of-speech tagging, text embeddings and 
    word embeddings. The package handles the Python dependencies management and 
    provides R-friendly wrappers for Flair's functionality. Users need Python (>= 3.9.0) 
    with PyTorch (>= 2.2.0), Transformers (>= 4.37.2), and Flair (>= 0.11.3) 
    installed in their system. The package automatically checks and validates the Python 
    environment during loading, ensuring all required dependencies are properly configured. 
Maintainer: Yen-Chieh Liao <davidycliao@gmail.com>
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.9.0), PyTorch (>= 2.2.0), 
    Transformers (>= 4.37.2), flair (>= 0.11.3),  Armadillo (>= 9.800)
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.3)
